Is there anything else I can help with?can we limit the ram and cpu utilization?Thought processThought processThat's a great question, especially on a corporate machine where resources may be shared. Here's what's generally possible:
Within the Claude desktop app:
As of my knowledge cutoff, there's no built-in setting in the Claude desktop app to cap CPU or RAM usage directly. For the latest on this, it's worth checking support.claude.ai as features may have been added.
At the OS level (Windows), you can limit it yourself:

Task Manager (quick & manual)

Open Task Manager → Details tab
Right-click the Claude process → Set Priority → "Below Normal" or "Low"
This reduces CPU priority so other apps aren't starved


CPU Affinity (limit which cores it uses)

Task Manager → Details → Right-click Claude → Set Affinity
Uncheck some CPU cores to restrict usage


Windows Job Objects / third-party tools

Tools like Process Lasso or BES (Battle Encoder Shirase) let you cap CPU % usage more precisely
These are useful if you want to enforce, say, a maximum of 20–30% CPU


RAM is harder to cap directly on Windows without enterprise tools, but keeping priority low generally helps prevent it from crowding out other apps.

My recommendation for a corporate laptop:

Set Claude's process priority to Below Normal
This is a simple, safe way to ensure it doesn't compete with your main work applications
